{{Quote|Run from the Devil!}}

'''Halloween Run''' is a [[:Category:PvP worlds|player-versus-player]] [[:Category:Game worlds|game world]], created by K1911jp_けーいち. One player assumes the role of ''the Devil'', and chases players on the other team, ''the Angels'', and can eliminate angels with their scythe. Angels can run and fly to avoid the Devil, before the timer runs out.

==Overview==
[[File:Halloween_run_bev.webp|thumb|left|A bird-eye-view of the map, for Halloween Run.]]
Halloween Run was initially released on October 14, 2024, as part of the [[Spookality]] [[world]] jam. The Devil must give chase to all of the Angels, while they try to evade.

===Game modifiers===
The Devil is selected at random for the game, but can also be manually selected.

The timer for the game can changed to the following units:
*30 seconds
*60 seconds
*90 seconds (1.5 minutes)
*120 seconds (2 minutes)
*180 seconds (3 minutes)
*300 seconds (5 minutes)

===Angels===
[[File:Halloween_runcandle.webp|thumb|right|Angels have a candle, which can be used to fly.]]
Angels must run away from the Devil! They are significantly small, making it easy to dodge the Devil and their attacks. Each angel has a candle that can be used, which can make the angel fly away for a short time. An angel wins the game if they successfully evade the devil throughout the duration of the game.
===Devil===
The user playing as the Devil chases the angels, and is significantly larger than the angels, and the buildings. A scythe can be equipped to eliminate angels out of reach. The scythe can emit a projectile that targets the angels. The devil can stomp through buildings and trees to catch the angels much quicker. The devil wins if all angels are caught or eliminated.

==Trivia==
* Halloween Run was one of ten winners, for VRChat's [[Spookality 2024]] world jam, part of the "Fractured Realm" series of worlds showcased by VRChat.

